This paper deals with efficiently computing frequent co-occurring terms in the results of a keyword query over multiple joined relations. This involves processing large amounts of data and extracting statistical information, which are typical tasks in the fields of databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and data science (cs.DS). The use of the MapReduce framework also suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper's emphasis on query expansion and refinement could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) applications.
